explanation: This solution uses a two-pointer approach to build the palindrome from the end of the string. It iterates through the string from right to left, inserting characters into a StringBuilder. If the first character of the StringBuilder does not match the current character, it increments the result and inserts the character at the beginning of the StringBuilder. This approach ensures that the palindrome is built in the minimum number of moves.

